1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 d5 4. cxd5 exd5 5. Bg5 c6 6. e3
h6 7. Bh4 Be6 {A speciality of Italien GM Luca Moroni. Black goes for quick
development of q-side pieces, although the Be6 is placed not optimally.} ({
The rare} 7... g5 8. Bg3 Bf5 {weakens the k-side too early and after the
simple} 9. Bd3 Bxd3 10. Qxd3 Nbd7 11. h4 Nh5 12. Nge2 $14 {White got the upper
hand in Lenic,L - Pavasovic,D Lichess.org INT 2020}) 8. Bd3 Nbd7 (8... Bd6 {
transposes to the position, that is mentioned in Chapter 6...Bd6, not 7...
Nbd7.}) 9. f3 $1 {A decent move. By making this move White not only prepares
the key e3-e4 advance but also secures a retreat of Bh4 in view of ...g7-g5.}
({The most common alternative is} 9. Nge2 {, and then Black goes for an
exchange of dark-squared bishop:} g5 10. Bg3 Nh5 11. h4 ({Also after} 11. Qc2
Nxg3 12. Nxg3 h5 13. O-O-O h4 {Black has a great play due to bishop pair and
space advantage on the k-side.}) 11... Nxg3 12. Nxg3 gxh4 13. Nf5 Qg5 {After ..
.0-0-0 Black will reach a harmonious setup. Donchenko,A - Andreikin,D Chess.
com INT 2022}) 9... g5 (9... Bd6 10. Nge2 Qe7 11. Qc2 c5 {Sorcinelli,A -
Moreno,C FICGS email 2013} 12. Bb5 $146 cxd4 13. Nxd4 Rc8 14. Qd3 $14 {The
weakness of Pd5 is especially significant now, when both Black's knights are
pinned.}) ({Too passive seems} 9... Be7 10. Nge2 O-O 11. O-O c5 ({Hardly
better is} 11... Re8 12. Nf4 Bd6 13. Nxe6 Rxe6 14. e4 $36 {White has the
bishop pair and now easily takes the upper hand in the centre. Mueller, S -
Platz,D Playchess.com INT 2021}) 12. Kh1 Re8 {This position occurred in
Sterling Carmona, F - Carrera Cabaneros, F Madrid 2012} {White could have
claimed the drawbacks of awkward Be6 by means of} 13. Nf4 $146 Qb6 14. Bb5 $36
{The Pd5 might fall soon.}) 10. Bf2 Bg7 ({After} 10... h5 11. Qc2 h4 12. Nge2
Nb6 13. O-O-O $14 {White has fully mobilized his forces ready to start active
measures with e3-e4. Ushenina,A - Cvitan,E Vrnjacka Banja 2021}) ({
Insufficient is also} 10... Qb6 {- the Qb6 is misplaced, and the king
shouldn't be safe on c8 either.} 11. a3 O-O-O 12. b4 Bd6 13. Nge2 Kb8 14. Rc1
$36 {David,A - Moroni,L Premium Chess Arena INT 2020}) (10... Bd6 11. Nge2 Qe7
{, as in Spiric,I - Kerecki,L Belgrade 2003} {can be naturally met with} 12. e4
$146 dxe4 13. fxe4 O-O-O 14. Qc2 Ng4 15. Bg1 $14 {Black has no compensation
for White's full control of the centre.}) 11. Nge2 h5 {The natural play by
both sides led to this position in Navara, D - Moroni, L Skopje 2018} {In my
opinion, the best way to meet Black's early extension on the k-side was} 12. h4
$1 $146 g4 13. Nf4 Qe7 14. Nxe6 Qxe6 15. Qe2 $36 {after 16.0-0-0 White will
reach a harmonious setup. At the same time, Black suffers from weak squares f4
and f5.} *

