$16 {Van Foreest,J - Bluebaum,M Tornelo INT 2021}) {I mostly like the
prophylactic} 15. b3 $146 ({Instead,} 15. h3 Nc4 {led to a double-edged play
in Ding,L - Bluebaum,M chess24.com INT 2021}) 15... a4 16. Nce2 Bd7 17. Qc2 $14
{Black has no real compensation for his weak Pc6, and ..e3-e4 is to follow
soon.}) 14. Ng3 {The best spot for the knight: It supports e3-e4 and can be
well placed on f5.} Bd6 15. a4 $5 $146 {By playing this White favourably fixes
the pawn structure on the q-side.} ({The previously played} 15. Nce2 c5 16. Nf5
Bf8 {was acceptable for Black in Duda, J - Salem, A Warsaw 2021}) 15... b4 16.
Bxa6 Rxa6 ({After} 16... bxc3 17. Bb7 cxb2 18. Rb1 Rb8 19. Bxc6 $14 {The Pb2
is neutralized, so White has a clear advantage due to powerful bishops and
superior centre.}) 17. Nce2 c5 {Black can hardly do without this move, but now
the isolated Pd5 is another weakness.} 18. b3 Ra8 19. dxc5 Nxc5 20. Nd4 $14 {
White has a slight, but long-lasting positional advantage due to strong
outpost d4.} *

